From Kenneth Ng Subject Re nuclear waste In article fred j mccall writes Just a bit off We don't reprocess nuclear fuel because what you get from the reprocessing plant is bomb grade It is also cheaper given current prices of things to simply fabricate new fuel rods rather than reprocess the old ones creating potentially dangerous materials from a national security point of view and then fabricate that back into fuel Fabricating with reprocessed plutonium may result in something that may go kind of boom but its hardly decent bomb grade If you want bomb grade plutonium use a research reactor not a power But if you want a bomb don't use plutonium use Kenneth Ng Please reply to for All this might be an elaborate simulation running in a little device sitting on someone's table Picard ST TNG